{
  "message": "fuzz(btrfs_chunk_mapping): grow corpus with 20 structured profile seeds\n\nExtend the fuzz_btrfs_chunk_mapping corpus from the original 6\nseeds (byte, empty, raid0, raid1, raid10, raid5, random) with 20\nhand-curated seeds that exercise specific corners of the BTRFS\nchunk-tree \u2192 physical-stripe mapping logic in fr-volumes (the\nreverse-direction of the chunk-allocator).\n\nThe fuzz target consumes a serialized BTRFS chunk-tree snapshot\nplus a logical address, runs the chunk lookup, and asserts the\nreturned stripe set matches the chunk's RAID profile. Each new\nseed is hand-tagged after a name-pattern that documents which\nbranch it covers:\n\nRAID profile coverage:\n  - seed_chunk_dup           \u2014 DUP profile (two identical mirrors)\n  - seed_chunk_raid0         \u2014 RAID-0 stripe (no redundancy)\n  - seed_chunk_raid1         \u2014 RAID-1 (single mirror)\n  - seed_chunk_raid10        \u2014 RAID-10 (mirror + stripe)\n  - seed_chunk_raid5         \u2014 RAID-5 (one parity stripe)\n\nSingle-profile sub-classifications (BLOCK_GROUP_SINGLE):\n  - seed_chunk_single_data   \u2014 DATA-only single\n  - seed_chunk_single_metadata \u2014 METADATA-only single\n  - seed_chunk_single_system \u2014 SYSTEM-only single\n\nMulti-chunk arrangements:\n  - seed_two_chunks_data_meta \u2014 adjacent DATA + METADATA chunks\n  - seed_five_chunks         \u2014 five-chunk tree exercising the\n                                lookup tree-walk\n  - seed_multi_raid_profile  \u2014 mixed RAID profiles in one tree\n\nBoundary / single-stripe inputs:\n  - seed_single_stripe       \u2014 minimal one-stripe chunk\n  - seed_just_logical_addr   \u2014 bare logical-address lookup with\n                                no chunk match (must return None)\n\nAdversarial / malformed inputs (must reject without panic):\n  - seed_stripe_zero_devid   \u2014 devid=0 (reserved, must reject)\n  - seed_truncated_below_key \u2014 record terminates before the key\n                                struct ends\n  - seed_truncated_mid_stripe \u2014 record terminates mid-stripe\n  - seed_wrong_key_type      \u2014 key type byte not CHUNK_ITEM\n  - seed_wrong_objectid      \u2014 objectid not the chunk-tree's\n                                expected sentinel\n  - seed_zero_length_chunk   \u2014 chunk_length == 0\n  - seed_zero_num_stripes    \u2014 num_stripes == 0\n  - seed_zero_stripe_len     \u2014 stripe_len == 0\n\nBringing the tracked corpus from 7 \u2192 27 should let libFuzzer's\nmutator hit deeper corners of the parser quickly instead of\nre-discovering basic profiles via random byte mutation.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>",
